org.spongepowered.api.data

Class AbstractDataManipulator<T extends DataManipulator<T>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.spongepowered.api.data.AbstractDataManipulator<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of implemented DataManipulator
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Comparable<T>, DataManipulator<T>, DataSerializable

    public abstract class AbstractDataManipulator<T extends DataManipulator<T>>
extends Object
implements DataManipulator<T>
    An abstract DataManipulator to extend for custom manipulators.

    To handle the creation of custom manipulators, it is recommended that extending this AbstractDataManipulator is used for the no-args constructor and then DataManipulator.fill(DataHolder) is called. Any access to the underlying implementation of a DataHolder needed should be handled by the implementing AbstractDataManipulator.
